In this article, President Trump delivers remarks from the Oval Office on Good Friday, acknowledging the suffering and death of Jesus Christ. He also discusses the ongoing battle against the "invisible enemy" of the coronavirus pandemic, praising healthcare workers and scientists for their efforts. Trump asks Americans to pray for healing, comfort, and strength during this challenging time. Bishop Harry Jackson then offers a prayer for the nation, asking for the plague to pass over and for unity among Americans. The article concludes with Trump thanking the bishop and wishing everyone a Happy Easter.